From: LiqXanMod Project <liqxanmod@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] liqxanmod: add CONFIG_LIQXANMOD_HYBRID Kconfig symbol

Introduces CONFIG_LIQXANMOD_HYBRID which gates the runtime workload
autodetect module and the dual-scheduler sysfs bridge. Selecting this
option compiles both the XanMod performance path and the Zen latency
path into the kernel; the active path is chosen at runtime by the
autodetect module based on observed workload characteristics.

Depends on SCHED_DEBUG so the sysfs tunables are accessible.

--- a/kernel/sched/Kconfig
+++ b/kernel/sched/Kconfig
@@ -1,6 +1,22 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
 menu "CPU Scheduler"
 
+config LIQXANMOD_HYBRID
+	bool "LiqXanMod hybrid scheduler autodetect"
+	depends on SCHED_DEBUG
+	default n
+	help
+	  Compile both the XanMod throughput-optimised scheduler path and the
+	  Zen/Liquorix low-latency scheduler path into a single kernel image.
+
+	  A lightweight in-kernel workload detector (drivers/liqxanmod/) samples
+	  CPU runqueue depth, wakeup frequency, and IRQ rate every 100 ms and
+	  switches the active scheduler profile via sysfs without requiring a
+	  reboot or kernel parameter change.
+
+	  Profiles: throughput (XanMod), latency (Zen), balanced (default).
+
+	  If unsure, say N and select a single-mode build instead.
+
 config SCHED_OMIT_FRAME_POINTER
 	bool "Omit frame pointer in scheduler hot paths"
 	depends on !FRAME_POINTER
